Housed in a building that dates back to the 14th century, the hotel is adorned with Murano glass chandeliers and antiques. The hotel is also close to some of Venice’s most iconic cultural attractions, including the famous Rialto Bridge.\n\nSan Cassiano Residenzia D’Epoca has a romantic history. As the former home of one of the greatest Venetian painters of the 19th century, much of its charm can be found in its décor. A reception desk is open 24 hours a day and facilities include internet, snack bar and tourist information.\n \nThe Best Bit\nThe main attraction of the San Cassiano Residenzia D’epoca is its excellent location.
